OL,3,CAssaulting shop workers to become
OL,4,Cspecific offence in new legislation
OL,6,FBut an initial response published last
OL,7,FOctober said: "The government is
OL,8,Fcommitted to supporting hardworking
OL,9,Fretail workers, who can suffer
OL,10,Fintolerable violence and abuse, but we
OL,11,Fdo not think more legislative change
OL,12,Fis required or will be most effective."
OL,14,FThe response added that the government
OL,15,Fhad already legislated in 2022 to make
OL,16,Fassaulting a "public-facing worker",
OL,17,Fincluding retail staff, an aggravated
OL,18,Foffence for sentencing "to emphasise
OL,19,Fthat these types of assaults are
OL,20,Ftotally unacceptable".
